Subject: Request for Custody Confirmation =E2=80=94 Imerman Devices (AC-2025-LON-=
004293)
Importance: High

=20

Dear Ms. Park,

I write as the Claimant in Zahmoul v Secretary of State for Justice & HMCTS=
 (Administrative Court reference AC-2025-LON-004293).

Your firm took custody of electronic devices identified as =E2=80=9CImerman mater=
ial=E2=80=9D on 13 April 2021 and is the last custodial holder of record. For ease=
 of reference, I attach copies of the contemporaneous open correspondence re=
lating to the delivery and custody of these devices.

Could you please confirm the following:
Whether these devices remain in your firm=E2=80=99s custody;
If not, the date on which they were released, and to whom;
A copy of the Court order or written authority under which any release occu=
rred;
An audit trail recording all movements, access, or transfers of the devices=
 while held by your firm.
For the avoidance of doubt, there is no issue of anonymity in this matter. =
Confirmation of the above is requested in the context of a public Judicial R=
eview into the administrative duties of public bodies and is of public inter=
est.

I would be grateful for your response by 16:00 on 12 December 2025.

Yours faithfully,
Nadia Zahmoul
Claimant
Zahmoul v Secretary of State for Justice & HMCTS
Administrative Court Reference: AC-2025-LON-004293

